<item>
            <title>[SPARK-22846] table&apos;s owner property in hive metastore is null</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SPARK-22846</link>
                <project id="12315420" key="SPARK">Spark</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;I met this issue after upgrading from spark 2.0.1 to spark 2.2.1.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;when creating table using spark sql or spark thriftserver, it occured that the table&apos;s owner info in metastore is null, which may cause other issue on table authentication. It may be a bug.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;After digging into the code, I found that in class HiveClientImpl:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;private&lt;/span&gt; val userName = state.getAuthenticator.getUserName
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;the result of state.getAuthenticator.getUserName is null, which would cause all operation on tables have a null username, such as method toHiveTable:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
 def toHiveTable(table: CatalogTable, userName: Option[&lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;String&lt;/span&gt;] = None): HiveTable = {
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;my create table command:  create table  datapm.test_xwc9(id string,name string);&lt;/p&gt;


</description>
                <environment>&lt;p&gt;spark 2.2.1, hive 0.14, hadoop 2.6.0&lt;/p&gt;</environment>
